class BasicInfo:
  def __init__(self,):
    self.rootPath = "./drive/MyDrive/final_project/"
    pass
  def getTrainImageList( self, ):
    # loading all image name
    trainImageListFile = open(  self.rootPath + "trainList.txt" )
    trainImageList = trainImageListFile.read().split('\n')
    trainImageList = np.array( trainImageList[ : -1 ] ) # remove the 
    return  trainImageList
  def getTrainDf(self,):
    trainDf = pd.read_csv( self.rootPath + "train.csv" )
    return trainDf
  def getTestItemList(self,):
    #!ls  ./drive/MyDrive/final_project/test > ./drive/MyDrive/final_project/testList.txt
    #!ls ./drive/MyDrive/final_project/testList.txt
    # loading all test image name
    testImageListFile = open(  self.rootPath + "testList.txt" )
    testImageList = testImageListFile.read().split('\n')
    testImageList = np.array( testImageList[:-2] ) # drop two no use record
    testItemList = np.unique( np.array( list( map(  lambda x : (x.split("_"))[0] ,  testImageList ) ) ) )
    return testItemList
  def getAppendFormat(self,):
    appendFormat = [ "_blue.png" , "_green.png" ,  "_red.png" , "_yellow.png" ]
    return appendFormat
  def getSplitLabelDf( self , trainDf ):
    tmpLabelArr = trainDf[ 'Label' ].apply( lambda x : list( map( int ,   x.split("|") ) ) )
    tmpDict = dict()
    for i in range( 19 ):
      tmpDict[i] = list()
    for labels in tmpLabelArr :
      for count in range(19):
        if count in labels :
          tmpDict[count].append(1)
        else:
          tmpDict[count].append(0)
    return pd.DataFrame(  tmpDict  )

def handleLabel( x ):
    if( '|' in x ) : 
        return False
    else : 
        return True

def PandasConcateLeftRight( left , right ):
    return pd.concat([ left.reset_index(drop=True), right.reset_index(drop=True)] , axis=1)

def getTrainDf(  ):
    df = PandasConcateLeftRight( rawTrainDf ,  rawTrainDf['Label'].apply(  handleLabel  ) )
    df.columns = [ 'ID' , 'Label' , "Bool" ]
    df = df[ df[ "Bool" ] == True ]
    df.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
    df = PandasConcateLeftRight( df['ID'] , df['Label'].apply( lambda x : int(x) ) )
    return df[ ['ID' , 'Label'] ]

def getColorImage( imageId , resizeImage512Path =  './resize512/'  ):
     imgArr = []
     for i in range( 4 ):
         imgArr.append( imread(  resizeImage512Path +  imageId + appendFormat[ i ] , as_gray=True  )  )
     return  cv2.merge (  imgArr  ) / 255

def getDecisionTreeModelAndScore(    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test ):
    model = DecisionTreeClassifier()                       # 2. instantiate model
    model.fit( x_train, y_train )                  # 3. fit model to data
    y_model = model.predict( x_test )             # 4. predict on new data
    score = accuracy_score( y_test , y_model)
    return  model , float( score )

model.add( MaxPooling2D( pool_size=(2,2) ) )

# 2nd Convolution layer
model.add( Conv2D( 64 , (3,3) )  )
model.add( Activation("relu") )
model.add( MaxPooling2D( pool_size=(2,2) ) )

# 3rd Convolution layer
model.add( Conv2D( 64 , (3,3) )  )
model.add( Activation("relu") )
model.add( MaxPooling2D( pool_size=(2,2) ) )

# fully connected layer
model.add(Flatten())
model.add( Dense(64) )
model.add( Activation("relu") )

# fully connected layer
model.add( Dense(64) )
model.add( Activation("relu") )

# fully connected layer
model.add( Dense(32) )
model.add( Activation("relu") )

# last fully connected layer
model.add(Dense(19))
model.add(Activation('softmax'))

Model Evaluation¶

In [ ]:
def getConfusionMaxtrix2DArray(   y_test ,  predicted   ):
    from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(list(y_test), predicted)
    return cm

def displayNLPConfusionMtrix(  y_test , predicted  ):
    from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
    cm = confusion_matrix(list(y_test), predicted)
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 15))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    cax = ax.matshow(cm)
    labels=list(np.unique(list(y_test)))
    plt.title('Confusion matrix of the classifier', y=-0.1)
    fig.colorbar(cax)
    ax.set_xticklabels([''] + labels, rotation=40)
    ax.set_yticklabels([''] + labels)
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.ylabel('True')
    plt.show()

For the confusion matrix of the classifier, the diagonal elements represent how the prediction equal to the true label. However, by observing our case, the three models' diagonal values are all low, hard to identify the features.
